(i) Pneumonia dataset- https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/paultimothymooney/chest-xray-pneumonia

(ii) Tuberculosis dataset- https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/tawsifurrahman/tuberculosis-tb-chest-xray-dataset

(iii) From here the dataset for COVID- https://doi.org/10.34740/kaggle/dsv/3122958

(iv) NIH dataset for atelectasis and Lung mass can be found from this article- Wang X, Peng Y, Lu L, Lu Z, Bagheri M, Summers RM:.ChestX-ray8: Hospital-scale Chest X-ray Database and Benchmarks on Weakly-Supervised Classification and Localization of Common Thorax Diseases. IEEE CVPR (2017)  
OR this can be downloaded from this website- https://www.nih.gov/news-events/news-releases/nih-clinical-center-provides-one-largest-publicly-available-chest-x-ray-datasets-scientific-community
